The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Atapattu rested

Colombo: Sri Lanka have named Mahela Jayawardene captain for the tour of Bangladesh starting this week. 

Jayawardene takes over from Maravan Atapattu who has been rested after struggling with back problems during the recent tri-series in Australia. Chaminda Vaas has been rested for the full tour, Muralidharan for the one-day series and Sanath Jayasuriya for the Tests. (Reuters) 




